name: Bev Weidner
bio: Pants and plants, books and nooks, thrifting and Swifting. But backwards.

social_posts.post_text: I threw the link to your Christmas mixtape in my feed if you need some vintage Nancy Meyers-style jazzy tunes in your life! (you do.) 🎄

Yesterday’s Friday Flotsam is cracking me up. Misheard lyrics! Your answers! 😂 My favorite is heartbean so far. 🤣Come tell me your best and worst misheard lyrics. You need the laugh today. (The blog link is in my profile!)
Truly not okay.😭😭😭

Potato, Leek and Gruyère Pie! 🥧You can definitely short cut this for a Tuesday. Or project recipe it for Sunday! Anything goes. It’s fabulous, savory and meditative. Recipeeeee! https://bevcooks.com/potato-leek-and-gruyere-pie/
Christmas Tree Focaccia! 🎄🎅🏻A complete embarrassment if this is not on your table this year. Or tonight. Or now. 🎄🍞✨ here you go! https://bevcooks.com/christmas-tree-focaccia/
Friday Flotsam is up and linked! We’re talking movies, skincare hoaxes (you tell me), and if you have a real Christmas tree or not. You know I need these details to thrive in this world. ✨

Creamy Rosemary Chicken with Linguine! ✨ for those nights when you need ease but you want to feel like you’re SOMEWHERE. *Sweats optional.* here’s the recipe! https://bevcooks.com/creamy-rosemary-chicken-with-linguine/

This summer I found some beautiful striped wallpaper (wallpaper!) at an estate sale for a BUCK and thought, “that’s the perfect Christmas wrapping paper!” and then almost forgot about it. Ha! But I didn’t forget, and here we are. Cute, huh? A buck! But not Uncle Buck. Never mind.

Creamy Dreamy Potato, Spinach and Sun-Dried Tomato Soup! ✨ it’s mostly vegetarian, minus the chicken stock. Sub it to your heart’s delight! Here ya go bunny: https://bevcooks.com/creamy-potato-spinach-and-sun-dried-tomato-soup/

Year nine (NINE!) of making these instagram-friendly books with @artifactuprising! I am dying. 😭 and yes, I have my yearly 15% off discount to offer once again. 👏🏻 use the code BEVCOOKS15 for anything for the rest of the year! (doesn’t include shipping, wedding services, bundle deals or gift cards) NINE. YEARS. (Don’t tell my jowls) Also the direct link is in my feed!🎄🎄

We’re making this Cinnamon Biscuit Bake on Christmas! (Autocorrect changed that to Christina.😂) Plus the Family Stone strata and a side of thick bacon.👌🏻 Good stuff. I put the link in my profile if you still need to brainstorm something cinnamony on Christmas morning. On Christina morning. (Tell me what you’re eating!)

Merry Merry Christmas! ✨🥂🎄🎅🏻Tell me what your favorite gift you GAVE was. That sentence looks and sounds odd to me. It might be the Pinot noir I’m drinking. Does it look weird to you? Why does it look weird! Anyway, fave (not fav) gift you gave. Spill it.

New year, new tunes! ✨ How else did you expect us to slide into 2023? 🎶 It’s a good one, too. Winter vibes, but still cheers you up a bit. It’s linked in my profile! (Also POLL: is your tree still up? Be honest.🫠)
That trench coat just gets smaaaaaller and smaaaaaller. Isn’t that the way it works?
2022 in books! Let’s talk favorites. Let’s compare lists. Let’s share our TBR pile! You know how we do. The post is linked in my profile!📚
Just your yearly reminder that nine years ago I looked like I ate a K-Mart and had cankles the size of nope. In other words, an…angelic? 🥴

Goofy, caring, intelligent, hilarious, kind, tender, loving, cute as buttons, and gassy. Very, very gassy, you guys. (I think they get that last part from their father.) Happy 9th, butter bean gremlins! 🎈🎈🎈 let’s not talk about what you’ve done to my jowls. 🎂

A few of my favorite things: Winter Edition! ✨Just in case you need a little cozy hygge inspo. Inexpensive every day goodies that make life just a little more 🧖🏼‍♀️🤗👌🏻. Here ya go! https://bevcooks.com/cozy-winter-favorite-things/

Here’s the Green Bean and Fennel Salad! Health enthusiasts will rejoice, but honestly this CRUNCH is enough to jazz any ol’ anyone. 🤗 I vowed not to overuse the word crunch today, so in the effort of not saying crunch, I’ll just link you to this crunchy salad. Crunch! https://bevcooks.com/green-bean-and-fennel-salad-with-parsley/
Crispy Chicken with Curly Pasta and Fresh Tomatoes! ✨This is basically a video of me trying to get eggshell out of a bowl. 🫠 https://bevcooks.com/crispy-chicken-with-curly-pasta-and-fresh-tomatoes/

The song has zero to do with this food. I’m just in a mood! ✨👌🏻 but if you are needing some veeeera simple rice and bean enchiladas, this is it. Total throw-together meal! Give it a go.👏🏻 https://bevcooks.com/2023/01/rice-and-bean-enchiladas/ also I still really, really love this song. 😭

Friday Flotsam is up for your weekend reading! This week we’re talking about saying Bloody Mary in the mirror three times (hard no), your favorite Jane Austen movies, and a few other things that will have you questioning why you even follow me. 🫠 link is in the profile! ✨

Creamy Beef Ravioli Soup with Kale! It’s definitely throw-together. And 100% slurpy. Hiiiiighly suggest this for whatever little snow storm coming your way!❄️❄️ https://bevcooks.com/2023/01/creamy-beef-ravioli-soup-with-kale/

Spinach and Pork Meatballs! ✨ but listen, the amount of herbs we also shove into these is obscene. Get so excited. (Also I CANNOT crack eggs with one hand. Just hopeless. 🥴) here you go! https://bevcooks.com/2023/01/spinach-and-pork-meatball-subs/

Slow Cooker Peanut Chicken Tacos! Giiiiiirl. 🤜🏻🤛🏻 Another banger in the “throw-together” category. Don’t diss the bottled sauce. There’s always a night that calls for it. And this is it. Get in that crunch! 👌🏻✨ https://bevcooks.com/2023/01/slow-cooker-peanut-chicken-tacos/

Friday Flotsam is up! 👏🏻We’re talking about my upcoming adventure overseas, and your brilliant long-haul flight tips. (Just ordered compression socks!) We also discuss EXTREMELY IMPORTANT (maybe) things that have been on my mind lately. Come on in, if you dare. 👀

Last week I posted my Sweaty Swiftie Armpitty running playlist! And then forgot to tell you here.🫠 Let me know what you think of it when you run to it. It’s so fun! I threw the link in my profile for ya. 🏃🏼‍♀️🏃🏼‍♀️🏃🏼‍♀️

Ahhh Valentine’s Day. The coziest and homebody-est of all holidays. I’m in the mood to sip some @breadandbutterwines Prosecco to start the evening. 🥂And then some Pinot Noir while making the SIMPLEST chocolates in the entire world. That’s right. #dontoverthinkit Grab some molds, melt some chocolate, fill and freeze. That’s it! And you can amp them up by adding nuts or cinnamon or heart jelly beans. Or nothing at all. Anything works. I’ll include a link in my profile for where you can find @breadandbutterwines for your Valentine’s Day! 🍷Cozy cozy up, y’all. #ad #breadandbutterwines

It’s Super Bowl Snack time! I have this hot ham and cheese dip that I’m obsessed with, and I have a feeling you’ll desperately need this on your party table. I’m using a variety of @crystalfarmscheeses, and it all gets baked and browned and bubbly and you’ll just flip out. So get ready. The recipe is in my comments, and I have a few more photos in my stories for you. Happy game day! (I’m in Kansas City, so you know who I’ll be rooting for. ;)) #ad #crystalfarmscheese 🧀🏈

Brothy Beans with Crusty Bread! 👌🏻👌🏻 you can make the bread from scratch, or not. I’m breezy! But hear me now, make this once and just watch it sky rocket to your weekly rotation. Takes 15 minutes! 👏🏻👌🏻 voila:: https://bevcooks.com/2023/02/brothy-beans-with-crusty-bread/ 🍞🫘🌿

Let’s not talk about how grown up Natalie is. Or Aaron. Ha! Never mind. (First Father/Daughter Girl Scouts Sock Hop Danceapalooza!) (I stayed home and watched father of the bride #2 with @amjodo) (bye)

If you start soon, you can make these happen for tomorrow’s game! They’re Aaron’s FAMOUS (in our heads) grilled buffalo wings and they are nothing short of phenom. 👌🏻We’re about to start the brine in an hour, and throw them on the smoker tomorrow! Freakin’ delish. Plus you just cannot deny wings on the Super Bowl. Ya can’t. (Who are you rooting for??) 🍗🏈🍻(linked in my profile!)

Before I casually head to Israel later today, how about some Valentine’s Day pizza! 👌🏻✨ pepperoni, artichoke HEARTS (haha), loads of herbs, it has it all. Plus we’re making our own dough! 💕 have a cozy cozy day. here’s the recipe for you. 👏🏻https://bevcooks.com/2023/02/pepperoni-and-artichoke-heart-pizza/

I’ve been in Israel for RIGHT AT 24 hours and it feels like an entire lifetime.✨ look at this place! I have so much to show you. We’ve already experienced the best hummus in the entire world, seen the Old City of Jerusalem today, eaten my weight in sesame seed goodies and learned a few cool new words. Sababa! It means, “that’s cool, bro. all good. no worries.” (I added the bro part) Also after eating 64 lunches today I said, “there’s no more room in the inn” and I’m pretty sure ZERO people got my reference. (I still laughed) I’m posting a lot more in stories if you want to follow along! Our dinner is at 9pm tonight so if you’ll excuse me I need to nap like the 84 year old I am. Bye. But stay tuned! @vibeisrael #vibetastes @touristisrael

Well hello, Nazareth! You are charming, creamy and delicious. ✨✨We took a food crawl through the narrow stone streets (one even had an old donkey walking trough thing!) of the city and it was rich, savory and absolutely perfect. These photos are mostly little snippets and scenes, but I’ll be showing you more food super soon. Soon! Well, as soon as my stomach digests. In April. 😬😴 @vibeisrael #vibetastes

We leave tomorrow night but I have sooooo much to show you! This has been an experience of an absolute lifetime, and I can’t wait to share more. But it’s a hundred billion o’clock and this 👵🏻 needs 😴. So for now, feast your eyes upon rugs, color, tile, moments, windows, life. 👌🏻✨ @vibeisrael #vibetastes

Our first couple of days in Israel! ✨We started at this GORGEOUS intimate hipster restaurant called @biciclettatlv for wine and all the food. So much atmosphere, so many turtlenecks (I counted) and so many plants! Absolute heaven for me. Then on Thursday we spent a good portion of the day in Jerusalem. The sites, the streets, the people, the incense! @touristisrael was just incredible as our guide. We ate so much! The Yehuda Market is beyond fascinating. Colorful, quaint and alive. I was obsessed. What a treasure to see all of it. And then we ended our first full day at the extremely chic and beautiful @opa_tlv for exquisite and creative vegan food. Who knew a root could be so fancy! What a day. And this was just the beginning…. (Round two coming in a few days!) @vibeisrael #vibetastes ✨✨

Friday Flotsam is back! I’m pretty much over jet lag (I think?), but ignore any typos. We’re discussing some important nonsense today, like the absurdity of autocorrect, Falkor’s uncomfortable roar, and the joy of throwing a boarding pass away. 🤗 it’s linked in my profile, if you can even see it because instagram looks completely different AGAIN. We’re fine.

Our second full day in Israel! (We’ll go in little pieces, okay?) I CANNOT express how beautiful a day it was. The sun, the conversation, obviously the food. (There was even children singing across a field and you KNOW I got all Sound of Music about it.) We spent the first half of the day on the BEAUTIFUL @farma_cultura where we had tea with the charming and adorable owners Gil and Nadav, perused the rows of rich vegetation, nibbled on herbs and berries like borderline psychos. Then we enjoyed the most wonderful, fresh, and vibrant vegan brunch I’ve ever experienced. Zero words for how that felt. An afternoon of chatting in the sun, sipping wine and taking photos with our darling @g.shraer, we were completely content. ✨ We ended the day with a very special Friday Night Dinner with the @alonraheli family! Like, IN THEIR HOME. They cooked every single bite, welcomed us in and shared with us their traditions. How amazing is that? Also @bar.damti’s laugh at the very end gives me so much joy. That is HER TO A T. 🤗 Okay, round three coming in a couple of days! @vibeisrael #vibetastes

The song has zero to do with the recipe. I’m just in a heavy Bjork mood this morning.✊🏻 Buuuut what I have for you today is a Broccoli Cheddar Chicken Puff Pastry Pie! 😂 so  many words. Each one 100% necessary. 👌🏻 there’s a short cut involved, but still very homey and doable any night of the week. Helloooo puff pastry! 🤤 https://bevcooks.com/2023/02/broccoli-cheddar-chicken-puff-pastry-pie/

Day three in Israel! 🇮🇱 We spent a GOOD portion of the day in Nazareth, and you guys, it was like going back in time. Like, biblical times. The teeny tiny streets, the stacked creamy buildings, the nibbles all along the way. @my.souk was our charming guide on the food tour, and when it was over we were stuffed, content and honestly blown away. Everyone had such a warmth! Historic and cozy, Nazareth was a true treasure. We ended at a fabulous lunch at @luna.bistro where we made grape leaves, drank wine and took in the city view. Words will never do it justice. Maybe this video does a little. A little, I said! @vibeisrael #vibetastes (day four coming soon!)
Your March mixtape is live! ✨👌🏻 as promised, you will feel like you’re in the middle of a Jane Austen movie. You cannot get upset at that. 👱🏻‍♀️(The link is in my profile!)

Friday Flotsam is up for your weekend reading! We’re talking about how I handle being at the doctor. The things I say. It’s out of control. (You do it, too, don’t look at me like that.) (it’s linked!)

Day four in Israel! 🇮🇱 it was a treasure, so pony (camel?) up. We explored the streets of Jaffa! Specifically the different neighborhoods that have various religions living side by side. We stepped into one BEAUTIFUL apartment with the most gorgeous windows I’ve ever seen. Hadas with @hadas.shmueli.nice2meet was our tour guide, and I was just so entranced by her. (She also inspired me to up my blazer game, hellooo) We spent a lively afternoon cooking (and dancing!) with @jaffastoriesandcoffee, a true, magnificent force of her own. Inspired and full, we then walked through the Jaffa market, taking in the abundance of colors and fragrances. We ended the night with a beach sunset stroll, then enjoyed an utterly wonderful dinner at @animartlv, which serves up fresh and vibrant Mediterranean cuisine. It was perfect, I’ll never recover. 😭 Day five coming soon! @vibeisrael #vibetastes

My Trip to Israel: Part One! I tried to keep it chill. I failed. There’s just so much to tell and show you! So go refill your coffee and let’s look at the first two days. (Thank you @g.shraer for the photo of me!) 🇮🇱 @vibeisrael #vibetastes (linked in my profile!)

Our last two days in Israel! 🇮🇱 and oh, we partied. (as best as a bunch of middle-aged moms know how 😂) We started the morning at a high-tech plant protein company called @chunk_foods, where we had SHOTS FIRST THING. (I’m telling you, Israelis throw down) along with mimosas. And we tasted their meatless product which was so fascinating! Then we met up with THEE charming Moni Kahlon of @bhukatours where he immediately whipped out bottles of white wine and a bunch of glasses FROM A CART right there on the street. He is my people. 👌🏻 We toured the Hatikvah Market and sampled one billion goodies, all before noon. The dancing in this video will give us away. 👌🏻🥂 after some rest, we met up for happy hour with nearly everyone we’d met, spent time with and fell in love with. The restaurant @abraxastlv was planty, moody and incredible. Such a night. Our last few hours were spent finishing out our souvenir shopping, a long walk along the beach (the pavement, not the sand, you know me) and one last lunch. I’m STILL full from that week. I’ll never forget it. Love you forever, @vibeisrael! #vibetastes 🇮🇱🇮🇱🇮🇱

Rigatoni with Roasted Tomatoes, Arugula and Bacon! Try and decide which word was your favorite. 🤗 It’s outrageous any night of the week, but I feel like being bossy and demand that you make it tonight. 👌🏻 here you go! https://bevcooks.com/2023/03/rigatoni-with-roasted-tomatoes-arugula-and-bacon/ (And yes I eventually straighten the pan, for my OCDers. 🥴)

Faaa-riday! Flotsam is up. And the url is telling me it’s the 361st Flotsam I’ve tortured you with. 😂 sorry? Today we’re talking about mirrored sunglasses (no), the names of generations, and I have something to ask. And I’m serious! It’s real. I want to make thrifting reels. Would you be into that? Tell me here, tell me there, I’m breezy!

Spiced Salmon and Rice Bowls! 👏🏻 Listen, this takes less than thirty minutes. Really. And that salmon marinade is problematic, just prepare thyself. Also, you’re seeing all that crunch right?? 😭👌🏻 https://bevcooks.com/2023/03/spiced-salmon-and-rice-bowls/
I see your posh spring break vacations and I raise you income taxes and dental cleanings. Take that! (Swipe if you need your ovaries to give you the bird.) 🥴

Spaghetti with Tomatoes, Anchovies and Shallots! Uuuuh, you don’t even know. The richness. The depth. The whole vibe! This is a fun change for pasta night, if you trust me. You do trust me, right? RIGHT?? https://bevcooks.com/2023/03/tomato-anchovy-pasta/

Faaaa-riday! 🥂🥂 Time for Flotsam. Today I’d LOVE to know all about your go-to karaoke song. What is it? I need all these deets. Tell me here, tell me there. (Mine’s a weird one but also why wouldn’t it be?)

My Trip to Israel: Part Two! And it is a DOOZY because I have zero self control. So many photos. But you just have to see it all! The nibbles, the views, the people, the houses. 👌🏻 Come on in and see how the next two days went.🫣@vibeisrael #vibetastes (linked!)

Rosemary Chicken Salad with Homemade Focaccia! ✨ Because the sun said hello for an entire three minutes this week and my soul jumped ahead to picnic season. Can you blame me? 🫣 here you go! https://bevcooks.com/2023/03/rosemary-chicken-salad-with-homemade-focaccia/

My first thrift reel! 👏🏻This edition: my dishes. (And one cup) I have a thing for vintage floral dishes, whether it be French-inspired blues and whites, soft pinks, tones of green, pops of dainty gold on the rims, I just love them. And you can find these beauties (for mega cheap!) at thrift stores, garage sales, estate sales, etc. They look stunning on a table with a bunch of flowers and small plates. Or at a picnic in the back yard! So much charm, I tell ya. Keep your eye open. They’re there. ✨

The most IT way to slurp your way into spring: Green Coconut Curry Noodle Soup with Mushrooms! 😭👌🏻 herbs for days, noodles for weeks, flavor for the rest of time. Giddy up! https://bevcooks.com/2023/03/green-coconut-curry-noodle-soup-with-mushrooms/

More soup! Okay but now we’re slurping tortellini with peas, arugula, mint and CRISPED prosciutto. 👌🏻ugh 👌🏻 it’s definitely a Throw-Together situation because we have garden bed prep to tackle! Skip skip 👉🏻https://bevcooks.com/2023/03/spinach-tortellini-soup-with-peas-arugula-and-prosciutto/
Friday Flotsam is up! 10% heavy, 90% fun. It’s basically a mullet. Go get in that link!👌🏻👌🏻
Aaron, SOMEDAY I’ll come out of my shell. Promise. 🥴 Happy 18th! 🥂💍(I still need you to clean your bedside table tho. 😘)

Your April mixtape awaits! This month, we’re cleaning up a bit. 🧹Getting seeds and seedlings in the ground. 🌱Organizing and fluffing and jushing. 🧺We clearly need a soundtrack to usher us along. Get on in the link in my profile! 🎧🎶
My final post on Israel! 🇮🇱We’re covering the last two days, so I’m gonna need you to grab your stretchy pants in solidarity because WHOA, GIRL. We party. (It’s linked!) @vibeisrael #vibetastes
We got so Eastered! 🥂💐🌱🐰🐣
A few Easter weekend snippets! 🐣 Swimming, the sunshine, mimosas, Eras tour friendship bracelets, neck hugging, mimosas, pancakes, a farm party, burgers, mimosas. Ya know, Easter essentials. 🥂

I’m changing it up today! (Ha ha. Ha?) We’re having an old-school type dinner. Pork chops seared to submission, the creamiest polenta, and the DREAMIEST herbed wine pan sauce. 😭 outrageous. Get in this luscious spring dinner! https://bevcooks.com/2023/04/pork-chops-over-polenta-with-an-herbed-wine-sauce/

Today I have a travel link roundup for ya! Everything I took on my international flight, some goodies I took to the beach last year, which also work perfectly for pool and park days. 🌞🕶️ it’s linked for you in my profile!

Let’s celebrate women! Women in wine. Women WITH wine. Women who own their own businesses and are actively building and creating a better and more beautiful world. I happen to have MANY fabulously talented women in my life, but I’m excited to celebrate four today. Four women who deserve praise and recognition (and hi, wine) for their hard work, brilliant minds and lovely hearts. First up, Stephanie from one of my favorite stores, @goldenandpine! Where clean lines meets cozy, she knows how to run a stunning home design store. (They even offer consultations!) Next up, Anna from @makefully_studios! A creative media studio owner for kids, she got her start with Jim Henson and Co. The woman knows how to make kids happy and inspired. (Trust me, mine are around her 80% of the time. :)) And lastly, Ashlee and Cindy with @kazoomedia! A charming boutique media strategy agency focused on paid media. (Like radio ads, ya know.;) Cindy owns and Ashlee is the head Media Director, and together they’ve built an empire like none other. I can’t believe (well actually I can) these women are in my life. I felt it only appropriate to gift the each a bottle of @breadandbutterwines, also led by the fiercely talented Linda Trotta! Women, we get it done. Cheers to my ladies! Can I have a little? 😉 #breadandbutterwines #dontoverthinkit #ad
It’s that one month a year when I pretend we’re living in the lush English countryside. 🌸🌺That apparently translated to the zoo for them.🫠

✨White Bean Salad on Toast!✨ Creamy, rustic, aromatic, a pinch of heat and a truckload of acidity. This, this, my friends, is an absolute favorite. A perfect spring lunch, or paired with a roast chicken for dinner. It’s just 👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻🌱🌱🌱 here you go! https://bevcooks.com/2023/04/white-bean-salad-on-toast/

Let’s talk about a few books! I promise there are ZERO spoilers in this post. And this might be the shortest reel I’ve ever posted. Ha! Okay book time: Happy and You Know It, Not a Happy Family and The Family Remains. 👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻 https://bevcooks.com/2023/04/bevs-imaginary-book-club-happy-and-you-know-it-not-a-happy-family-and-the-family-remains/

I forgot to post this on Friday, so Monday it is! 😂🥴 I will say, your comments on Friday Flotsam were so good, so fulfilling, so funny. So thanks! I have a lot ahead of me. The post is linked for your Monday reading! (Basically you guys I didn’t know what tea meant.🫠🫠)
Our tree is having its big glamorous moment and you need to experience it with me. ✨

Lemon and Poppy Seed Scones! ✨ the amount of times I double checked to make sure that didn’t say poopy seeds is something else. Still not convinced it doesn’t say poopy. 🥴 So yeah. Here’s the recipe if you needs some delicious fluffy scones in your face! https://bevcooks.com/2023/04/lemon-poppy-seed-scones/

Homemade Hummus! At last, I get it. I know. I have a simple recipe on the blog today, plus a few tips I smuggled back from Israel! Guaranteed gorgeousness. Here! 👉🏻https://bevcooks.com/2023/04/homemade-hummus/
Friday Flotsam is up! We’re talking about cities with Ferris Wheels, new garage doors and old Taylor Swift gems. (let me have this.) it’s linked in the bio!
Your May mixtape is up! It’s very jazzy and light and breezy and mood boosting. Don’t make me beg. https://bevcooks.com/2023/05/monthly-mixtape-climbing-vines-and-sippin-wine/ 🎶🎧🌱🌸

I’m about to power wash the playhouse today and realized it’s been three years! The kids are now teenagers and my jowls are unhappy with this. So many of you have built your own version of ours and that makes me so happy. Three years! 🌞🕶️🌸 here’s the link (also in profile) if you’re feeling ambitious this summer. 🔨 https://bevcooks.com/2020/06/summers-canceled-so-we-built-a-playhouse/

Friday Flotsam is up! Let’s talk about gleeking. 😂🥴 and a famous song that makes me cringe. And hollyhocks! I need your advice because my life has suddenly gone in a new direction. Here! https://bevcooks.com/2023/05/friday-flotsam-369/

Here’s the Pappardelle with Veggies! I’ve been trying to make this reel for a week but instagram no longer works. 🙄 but I got it made anyway! 👌🏻voila! https://bevcooks.com/2023/05/pappardelle-with-veggies-and-herbs/

Kale Salad with Smoked Salmon, Radishes and Cucumber! My go-to lunch salad lately. Creamy, earthy, sharp, crunchy. 👌🏻 also autocorrect just changed kale to Jake. Jake salad. 😂 it’s official. https://bevcooks.com/2023/05/kale-salad-with-smoked-salmon-radishes-and-cucumber/

Sheet Pan Dinner night! We have chicken (thighs!), potatoes, red bell, red onion, your blistered soul. 👌🏻 It’s truly a rustic and textured situation that will leave you giddy. Family friendly and eaaaaasy, bay-buh. Here you go! https://bevcooks.com/2023/05/sheet-pan-dinner-with-chicken-peppers-and-potatoes/

Friday Flotsam is up! And the link tells me it’s the 370th Flotsam post I’ve written. THREE HUNDRED AND SEVENTY I AM SO SORRY. 🫠 so after all this time, who still isn’t quite sure what flotsam even is? ‘Fess up!

The other night I had some friends over to share a bottle of @breadandbutterwines Sauvignon Blanc with a homemade lemon butter out in our garden and I’m STILL dreaming about it. ✨Listen up because this is so simple.
